President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Mauro Morales as the Staff Director of the United States Commission on Civil Rights, and Daniel Weiss as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Mauro Morales is currently the Assistant Director in the Office of Public Engagement at the Office of Personnel Management and has previous experience in law and government. Daniel Weiss is the Managing Partner of a private equity firm and has experience in law and various organizations.